  "description": "¶Entry conditions You should be comfortable with groups and monoids.\n¶Definitions A ring (R,+,⋅,0,1)(R, +, \\cdot, 0, 1) is a set RR with two binary operations satisfying:\n(R,+,0)(R, +, 0) is an abelian group. (R,⋅,1)(R, \\cdot, 1) is a monoid. Multiplication distributes over addition: a⋅(b+c)=a⋅b+a⋅ca \\cdot (b + c) = a \\cdot b + a \\cdot c and (b+c)⋅a=b⋅a+c⋅a(b + c) \\cdot a = b \\cdot a + c \\cdot a. If ⋅\\cdot is also commutative, the ring is commutative.\n",
